programme.title: DRY AGED VENISON
programme.desc: We Dry Aged Venison Hind Legs for 62 Days Seasoned it with HuntChef Canadian Carnivore then Added it to a Flavor Packed Stir Fry with Chicken of the Woods Mushrooms Topped it with Sunny Side Eggs and HuntChef Feather Duster! Dry Aged Perfection!!

programme.title: VENISON PIZZA BURGERS
programme.desc: Find out what happens when Little Italy meets WILD FLAVOR! Join HuntChef and the Experience Hunt hunters in West Central Illinois as they bring together wild caught venison, peppers, onions, olives, mushrooms, pepperoni, and buffalo mozzarella into double-stacked Venison Pizza Burgers that you don't want to miss! The HuntChef Hot Italian Sausage Kit will transform any wild game into mouth-watering Italian cuisine! #EATWHATYOUKILL

programme.title: TWO VENISON SOUPS
programme.desc: HuntChef brings you two awesome venison soups from the Experience Hunt camp in West Central Illinois. Chef cuts up venison bottom round for chili and venison sirloin for steak & potato soup. The chili is packed with #wildflavor, from the onions, to the Taco Takedown, Smokey Bayou, and Ten Ring seasoning. The potato & leek soup is stuffed with leeks, onions, mushrooms, baked potatoes, and flavored with Canadian Carnivore and Party Fowl. These dishes will fill the belly and keep hunters warm out in the woods or on the stand. #EATWHATYOUKILL

programme.title: WHITETAIL HIND LEG HAM
programme.desc: In this episode, HuntChef goes through the steps to cure venison hind legs in brine to make amazing venison ham. Learn how to brine, inject, and smoke your venison using the HuntChef Brine Kit to produce an amazing ham perfect for the holidays, or even just on a sammich. #EATWHATYOUKILL

programme.title: VENISON NECK PASTA
programme.desc: HuntChef feeds a camp full of hungry veteran hunters with a filling one-pot pasta dish using one of his favorite cuts of venison -- the neck roast. Fresh onions and garlic, mushrooms, and pepperoni bring layers of #wildflavor to the red wine marinara sauce, while the HuntChef Hot Italian Sausage Mix brings makes the venison neck sing! Chef finishes off the dish with half and half, oregano, and parmesan cheese to make a flavorful and creamy, alfredo-style pasta dish. Bon Appétit and #EATWHATYOUKILL!

programme.title: VENISON CAMP ROAST
programme.desc: HuntChef cooks up a simple but delicious meal of venison heart and back strap for the Experience Hunt hunters. Some Big Sexy Beast Rub and a little bit of olive oil are all you need to bring big #wildflavor to this easy venison roast. Served with a side of fried potatoes and onions dusted with All Dusted Up round out the meal. This meal is an easy and delicious way to #EATWHATYOUKILL.

programme.title: LOUISIANA STYLE VENISON SHANKS
programme.desc: Get a taste of Southern Louisiana cuisine with this Venison Shank dish. HuntChef throws down some lightly breaded venison shanks and brings the #wildflavor Cajun-style with Smokey Bayou. Meanwhile, a bacon and brown ale-infused shrimp creole--brimming with onions, tomato, garlic, roasted chilis, beans, red wine, and more of that sweet, Southern Smokey Bayou--completes the dish. You don't have to be born on the bayou to eat like you were. #EATWHATYOUKILL

programme.title: COUNTRY FRIED VENISON TACOS
programme.desc: A little bit Southern, a little bit Tex-Mex, HuntChef throws down some #wildflavor with these Country Fried Venison Tacos. Sliced venison fillets are seasoned with HuntChef Ten Ring Speed Beef Rub and Taco Takedown, bathed in buttermilk, and dredged in flour before frying to a crispy golden brown. Meanwhile, the Experience Hunters make fresh salsa from tomatoes, jalapenos, avocado, cilantro, and lime. It all comes together to build layers of #wildflavor in handmade tacos, topped with everything from nacho cheese sauce to rice to refried beans! #EATWHATYOUKILL

programme.title: WILD FLAVOR POTATO BOMBS
programme.desc: Talk about layers of #wildflavor! These potato bombs bring a whole new meaning to "loaded baked potatoes!" These baked potatoes are wrapped in bacon and stuffed with cheese, venison bacon, maple sausage, and BBQ snack sticks. HuntChef takes it further using All Dusted Up, Low Down & Dirty, and Feather Duster, then tops it off with his Memphis-style BBQ sauce. This venison-stuffed appetizer is a meal in and of itself! #EATWHATYOUKILL

programme.title: REDNECK RAMEN
programme.desc: Forget that Styrofoam cup of instant noodles! HuntChef throws away the salty flavor packets and turns instant ramen into Redneck Ramen! Canadian Carnivore brings out the #wildflavor in a pull-apart venison roast, perfect for topping your ramen or stuffing your venison wontons. Chef finishes off the wontons with ginger and cream cheese, before bringing a bit of heat to the ramen with HuntChef Jalapeno Sausage Mix. Broccoli, bell peppers, garlic, soy sauce, cream cheese, and lime come together to make a creamy noodle dish, topped with thin sliced radish, peanuts, wasabi peas, and more venison! Sayonara salty noodles! #EATWHATYOUKILL

programme.title: VENISON BACON
programme.desc: HuntChef walks through using the HuntChef Brine Kit and uses a dry-cure method to turn this mixture of ground pork and ground venison into a sweet and savory Venison Bacon. You can choose your own adventure by adding maple syrup or Straight Outta Pontchartrain. After makin' the bacon, Chef also cooks up some Feather Duster eggs and toast for the classic American breakfast. It's easy to start your day with #wildflavor when you know how to #EATWHATYOUKILL.

programme.title: Turkey Leg Soup
programme.desc: HuntChef aims to make a wild flavor soup so good that hunters will think twice about just breasting out their birds and stop leaving the legs behind! This soup is a wild take on the classic chicken noodle soup, with a carrot, onion, garlic, and celery stock. HuntChef's Party Fowl seasoning makes the bird sing, while Ten Ring and All Dusted Up deliver the one-two finishing combo. The bowl is rounded out with hearty lima beans and mushrooms, aromatic herbs, and tasty noodles. This is turkey soup for the hunter's soul!

programme.title: Fried Walleye & Spring Preserves
programme.desc: HuntChef shows you how to close out the spring season with a wild flavor-style Pennsylvania harvest! This Lake Erie walleye fillet pairs perfect with HuntChef's Straight Outta the Bay! Served with a side dish of gathered Chicken of the Woods mushrooms and Pennsylvania pickled ramps, all fried up with green onions -- and flavored to perfection with Canadian Carnivore and Party Fowl. And we haven't event mentioned the fluffy and delicious bed of wild rice pilaf. You always start summer with a full stomach when you #EATWHATYOUKILL.

programme.title: Old Green Plane | Episode 2 | Colby Coash
programme.desc:
In this episode, Craig and Collin travel with their guest, former state senator and actor, Colby Coash.
Colby Coash, former State legislator who was instrumental in getting the death penalty repealed in the state of Nebraska which earned him the national spotlight and landed him on The Daily Show. He is also a strong supporter of craft breweries in Nebraska, having passed legislation to help brewers locally.
Colby is also an actor, and has a role in a new film, La Flamme Rouge with Clint Howard and has appeared in many movies and shows over the years.
Craig, Collin, and Colby travel around the city of Lincoln and Colby even gets to fly N9962T for a bit on our way to Zepplin's a local barbecue "hidden gem" located near the airport in Lincoln, Nebraska.

programme.desc:

Aaron Davis is a nationally known keynote speaker. Davis, known as an expert on attitude (Attitude of a Champion) is also an author having authored two books with his third set to release in early 2020.
Davis is also a former member of the University of Nebraska Cornhusker Football team, and was a member of their 1994 National Championship team.

programme.desc:
On this episode of Old Green Plane, Craig and Collin take up Forbes Writer, Nicole Fisher on our way to survey the flood damage in Nebraska and then return to one of the best burger places in all of Nebraska- Honest Abes.
Besides being a Forbes writer, who specializes in trends in and around Health and Human rights, Nicole is also a Health and Human rights activist having founded her firm HHR Strategies that focuses on solving the biggest health challenges of the day.
Watch as Craig, Collin, and Nicole travel to areas near Nebraska City, Nebraska to survey the extensive flooding damage of 2019.

programme.title: What is Old Green Plane all about?
programme.desc:
Old Green Plane is an interview and travel show with our two hosts, Collin Caneva and Craig Spilker, that takes place in a 1960 Cessna 182D Skylane airplane. In 2015, Collin Caneva came into ownership of his Father's plane, which before that day, he had no clue where the plane was or who the plane was owned by. This was a plane that, as a child, Collin flew in with his Father on his many travels.
After taking ownership and re-certifying himself as a pilot, Collin and Craig began using the plane for business trips but it would also turn into trips where they'd find cool and unique places and people along the way.
It wasn't long before both Craig and Collin felt a need for a show where they get to meet and talk with interesting people doing interesting things, visit interesting places and show off their local and unique cuisine.
That's why we created Old Green Plane, to tell the story of both the people they meet and the places they go.
Old Green Plane is also about a desire to push beyond the "uncomfortable" and find those unique stories of the people and places they visit and then try to find those unifying and commonalities between us all but in a four seater, 1960-vintage airplane.
Come fly with us.

programme.title: Old Green Plane | Episode 4 | OGP Upgrades and Updates
programme.desc:
In this episode, we walk you through our camera and sound upgrades. At the beginning of 2020, we took OldGreenPlane out of service and Silverhawk Aviation upgraded our cameras, replaced the firewall, new ceiling panel, cleaned out outdated/unused wiring, dialed in the new engine, and fixed some miscellaneous corrosion.
Follow along as we walk you around the plane during and after the project!

programme.title: Old Green Plane | Episode 5 | The Rogers' Family
programme.desc:
Season 1 | Ep 5
In this episode, shot back in August of 2019, Collin and Craig fly to Spearfish, South Dakota to the home of the Rogers' family. Their daughter, Madelaine, has cystic fibrosis and she and her mother, Laurie, and her sister, Olivia, join Craig and Collin as they talk about their journey with CF as well as their foundation and yearly fundraiser - 'Moon'light for M&M.
Watch as Craig and Collin travel over the Black Hills of South Dakota where Collin was raised. They then travel to Killian's Food and Drink in Spearfish, South Dakota for some great food and conversation.
Special thanks to Eagle Aviation in Spearfish as well as Killian's Food and Drink in Spearfish who were both gracious enough to host us.
To Donate (if you can) please visit: https://sites.google.com/site/moonlight4mm/

programme.desc:
Season 1 | Ep 6
In this episode we stay in the Black Hills of South Dakota with our guest, and Mayor of Deadwood (South Dakota), David Ruth Jr.
Watch as Collin and Craig take Mayor Ruth Jr. up in 62tango and fly over the crowds of Sturgis (shot in August of 2019), Deadwood, and the Black Hills of South Dakota and then have some amazing dinner in downtown Deadwood. Learn about the history of the city through their Mayor's eyes and learn more about our pilot Collin Caneva's home.
Special thanks to the Deadwood Social Club and Saloon 10 for being so generous. A special thanks also goes to the City of Deadwood, and Eagle Aviation in Spearfish, South Dakota.

programme.desc:

Watch as Collin and Craig take Julie in OGP and head to the lake for some fun in the outdoors.

programme.title: Old Green Plane | ep 8 | Anthony Goins
programme.desc:
In this episode our guest is former Marine, author, business executive, CEO of Capital Cigar Lounge, and current Director of Economic Development for the State of Nebraska, Anthony Goins.
In this episode fly along as Collin and Craig take Anthony along as we travel to Norfolk Nebraska and ride along in our "unique" courtesy car. We also get to bring along the Mayor of Norfolk, Josh Moenning and Senator Mike Flood.

programme.desc:
In this episode of Old Green Plane, fly along as we take our guest and meditative expert Angie Caneva on a one of a kind trip back in history.
Learn simple ways you can relax as we meditate along with Angie, who is also a meditative expert on Carbon Unwind.
This episode is sure to intrigue and relax you.

programme.title: Old Green Plane | ep 10 | Jon 'Jughead' Counsell
programme.desc:
In this episode of Old Green Plane, Collin and Craig get to fly in formation with Military Aviation and jet fighter himself, Jon 'Jughead' Counsell.
Collin and Craig fly in formation with Jughead as flight commander but also with two Nebraska RedStar Formation fliers, Kurt Muhle and Keith Harbour.
Watch as Jughead and his team teach Collin and Craig about the ways to fly in formation safely while also having some amazing fun.

programme.title: Old Green Plane | ep 11 | Rob Scholl & Textron Aviation
programme.desc:
In this the eleventh episode of Old Green Plane, Collin and Craig travel to Wichita Kansas and the home of Textron Cessna Aviation where they get to meet with Textron's SVP of Sales and Flight Logistics, Rob Scholl.
Rob takes Collin and Craig on an amazing "behind the scenes" look at the newest in Textron's planes as well as how they're made.
Most of all, Collin gets to fly over the very airfield where his father first received the 'Old Green Plane' back in 1960.
This is every aviators dream and you won't want to miss this one.

programme.title: Old Green Plane | ep 12 | The Trip to Cheyenne
programme.desc:
This episode Old Green Plane is all about adversity. How do you deal with adversity? As a pilot? As a person?
How would you deal with very high winds and erratic, quickly changing weather?

programme.desc: Alakan Sitka Deer backstraps grilled over mesquite lump coal and drizzled over by fire melted blue cheese and crumbled smoked bacon. Try this with any venison backstrap and savor every bite!

programme.desc: Salmon is hard to cook wrong, but it's also hard to cook just right. This is our favorite recipe of all the different ways to cook salmon and it is super easy. Cedar, smoke, Rosemary and Thyme. Bring on the compliments after you serve this to your guests!

programme.title: Venison Hangover Burger w/Quail Eggs
programme.desc: This is one of our absolute best burger recipe we've ever served up. We use whitetail venison for this video and pair it up with grilled sweet onion, Nueske's smoked bacon, smokehouse cheddar and provolone, along with a trio of sunny-side up quail eggs on top. Oh, and let's not forget a little bit of barbecue sauce to dress it up a little more. Perfection in a toasted bun!

programme.title: Hawaii Wild Boar And Spearfishing
programme.desc: The Green Way Outdoors team heads to the island of Maui to hunt for wild pigs and do some spearfishing. You won't believe the double shot Kyle makes on pigs!

programme.title: Alaska Sockeye Salmon
programme.desc: Kyle Green heads to Alaska to fish for sockeye salmon with his cousin William, and buddy Mike. They catch limits every day and enjoy the most beautiful scenery in the world!

programme.title: High Mountain Chukar
programme.desc: The Green Way Outdoors team heads to the mountains in Eastern Washington to target chukar. This frustrating upland bird makes for a great adventure!

programme.title: Channel Islands Fishing
programme.desc: The Green Way Outdoors team heads out to the Channel Islands National Park 30 miles offshore to fish for halibut and whitefish. The amount of fish they see while spearfishing is incredible!

programme.title: Hawaii Axis Deer
programme.desc: The Green Way Outdoors team heads to the island of Maui to hunt Axis Deer! Jeff gets a giant buck and Kyle embarks on an unforgettable journey.

programme.title: Snake River Cutthroat
programme.desc: Kyle Green heads to the Snake River in Idaho to fish for rainbow trout and work with the DNR to help save the cutthroat trout. The management of this fishery is a touchy subject, but the team follows the science to get real answers!

programme.title: The Great Washington Bird Hunt
programme.desc: The Green Way Outdoors team heads to Washington State to hunt for ducks and quail. Lots of birds and lots of laughs in this high-action episode!

programme.title: Inland Lake Ice Fishing
programme.desc: The Green Way Outdoors team targets northern pike through the ice with their buddy Scott Slater. The big one they catch is a beauty!

programme.title: Noodling Giant Catfish
programme.desc: The Green Way Outdoors team heads down to Texas to try their hand at noodling. Did they catch a new Texas state record blue cat?

programme.title: Manistee River King Salmon
programme.desc: The Green Way Outdoors heads to the Manistee River in Northern Michigan to target King Salmon! Jeff catches an absolute monster!

programme.title: Prehistoric Paddlefish
programme.desc: Kyle Green travels to Oklahoma to fish for a prehistoric dinosaur called the paddlefish. He never expected the action to be this good!

programme.title: Giant Lake Sturgeon
programme.desc: The Green Way Outdoors team head out on the St Clair river to target giant lake sturgeon with their buddy Mitch. The monster Kyle caught was way over the slot limit!

programme.title: The Florida Kingfish
programme.desc: Kyle Green travels to Florida with his Sea-Doo FishPro Trophy to target kingfish, snook and giant Tarpon! He meets up with Frank Viola and Bri Andrassy who take Kyle out of his freshwater comfort zone. They go 7 miles out to sea, fish under docks, and everything in between. Don't miss the biggest fish we have ever featured on our show!

programme.title: THE MAINE MOOSE
programme.desc: The chances of getting drawn for moose tag in the state of Maine is slim to none. However, since the winter tick problem has been getting so bad in moose populations the department of fish and game has had to open up more opportunity for hunters to kill these ticks with moose hunting. How does that work?

programme.title: ALAKSA SOCKEYE SALMON
programme.desc: The last frontier is not a place for the faint of heart. It's full of natural resources that can harvested if you're willing to go on an adventure for it! Kyle and his cousin, William, go out for the sought after, sockeye salmon. Kyle is learning a new method of fishing that could be frowned upon if practiced in other places of North America. This method is called flossing.

programme.title: THE SNAKEHEAD FISH
programme.desc: A fish that heals you? Many cultures believe that the snakehead fish has healing capabilities that can even cure cancer. That is part of the reason why this invasive species ended up in the North American waterways. programme.title: Slow down for more birds
programme.desc:
You set the pace in the field, and if you're in a rush so is your dog. That means less time in a scent cone and more missed birds.
Scott Linden of Wingshooting USA TV shows you how, and explains why, you should dial things down a bit when it comes to covering a field or covert.
If you want more tips on dog training and bird hunting, go to: www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: Hunting dog tailgate exam, part one
programme.desc:
Your best hunting partner needs some TLC ... especially after a hunt. wingshooting USA TV host Scott Linden provides the first part of three, helping you check him from nose tip to tail and ensure he's healthy, safe, and ready to go the next day.
Today, it's all about your dog's coat. We'll cover why it's important to get him off the ground, how "training" for the exam is critical, and what to look for from injuries to parasites. Your dog will stay healthier, well-rested, and ready to go the next day.
You'll also see some fun and exciting bird hunting footage from a hunt where the tailgate exam became crucial.

programme.title: Take a newcomer hunting - here's how
programme.desc:
Safety first, but then what? Author and TV host Scott Linden outlines some ways to encourage, motivate, and then help a new hunter on their first hunt.
From weather to shooting tips, to interacting with the dog, and what really counts on the hunt, Scott offers suggestions to ensure everyone has fun.
For more tips on hunting, dog training, and finding places to go: www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: Identify your best prospect for a new hunter
programme.desc:
Picking the right new hunting partner is an art and a science ... and while there's no wrong way, some ways are righter than others. Author/TV host Scott Linden outlines some tips on finding the right person, how to set expectations, and what to tell them - and show them - before you make "the ask."
For more tips, go to www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: The new-hunter best recruiter is your dog!
programme.desc:
Who doesn't love hunting dogs? The magic of their performance, excitement, and the adrenaline rush of a flush! One easy way to start a new hunter is to invite them to help train your dog.
Simple, short, convenient - there's no downside. And who wouldn't appreciate a little help with dog training?
Plus, some cool footage of a hunt with excellent dog works.
For more on starting a hunter, finding places to hunt, and dog training, go to www.findbirdhuntingspots.com.

programme.title: Ideas for finding new places to hunt
programme.desc:
Find upland birds on waterfowl production areas, and more tips on accessing public hunting areas are two of the topics ... as well as a great place to headquarter: Huron, South Dakota.
Watch some exciting bird hunting footage, too.
Find more information at www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: Tailgate exam, part 2: wheels
programme.desc:
Part two covers your dog's "wheels," his feet. Enure a fantastic hunt tomorrow by keeping his feet healthy and injury-free with these step-by-step, toe-by-toe instructions.
Geet the entire exam in written form at HappyJackInc.com.

programme.title: Be nice, see where it gets you
programme.desc:
Walk-in hunting spots are not always easy to find. Here's an example of how to find them and the bonuses you might find along the way.
From hunting with a pro baseball player, to finding a black pheasant, to discovering new public-access spots in Huron, SD, there's a few lessons here.
Plus, some fun footage of a South Dakota pheasant hunt.
For more tips, go to www.findbirdhuntingspots.com

programme.title: Peak performance on Day Two: feed your dog strategically
programme.desc:
In the first 20 days of this season, my wirehair Flick had already hunted over 200 miles. He still scratches the RV door every morning, eager for another day of chukar chasing and quail quests.
I manage to keep up (mostly) with coffee and pain reliever. Flick, on the other paw, gets his stamina from Dr. Tim's dog food.
If your dog hunts multiple days in a row, it might be worth a look at how important food is to his performance. I asked Doctor Tim Hunt to share his thoughts on that, but first, a hunting story.

programme.title: Tailgate exam, Part 3: His steering wheel
programme.desc:
Okay, we've checked his body, his feet. But the tailgate exam isn't over until you've checked a dog's head – the steering wheel of your hunting machine. Like your truck, you're not getting very far without one! Put off that tall cold one for a couple more minutes. You'll have a fully-functioning hunting partner for the next day … and you won't die of thirst!
In this video, I'll show you where to look, what to look for and why ... and also how to remedy most common issues that might kibosh your next day's hunt, from getting stuff out of eyes and ears, to ensuring weeds and crud stay outta those places and more!
I'll take you step-by-step through all the deep, dark places that harbor danger and irritation on your dog's head so he's ready and rested for the next day's hunt.
And if you need remedies for any of the problems outlined, you can find them at www.happyjackinc.com.

programme.title: Get high, become a better bird hunter
programme.desc:
Not like that! I mean, boost your altitude - even just a bit - and you'll be able to keep a closer eye on your dog. If you're paying attention, you'll have a crucial half-second extra to get ready for a safe, sure shot.
I'll show you how - what you might use to get "up there" a little, what to look for in your dog's behavior, and why it's worth the effort.

programme.title: What's in my vest ... and why
programme.desc:
"Don't leave home without" is more than a cliche' from a TV commercial. What should you take on your next bird hunt, for you and your dog? Here's some advice on critical stuff, and what you might leave home ... without jeopardizing your safety or comfort - or you're dog's!
Somewhere in my personal vest is everything I need to shoot as well as possible (no smart remarks, please), stay found or get found, keep my dog safe and healthy, and help me survive a night or two in an emergency.
I'll show you all of it, and how to keep it from getting lost somewhere in the middle of nowhere!

programme.title: Your dog hurts - here's why
programme.desc:
I seem to be getting a lot of related questions since the season ended – most about aches and pains in our four-footed hunting buddies. And us!
The difference is, dogs won't show it like we do, with gripes and limping, complaints and wincing. They are way too loyal and hard working. It's why we love 'em.
You might already know this, but veterinarians tell me dogs seldom show pain. What they do, is slow down. Their pace in the field drags, they're slow to get out of their crate.
Maybe they won't jump onto your tailgate or training table.
That's probably arthritis, and it affects most dogs over eight years old. But here's the scary part: twenty percent of dogs show signs as early as one year old.
In this video, I'll show you how to prevent arthritis, manage it if your dog already has it, and what to avoid so he doesn't get it prematurely!

programme.title: Fuel your bird dog's peak performance ... but NOT with carbs!
programme.desc:
We hunt to watch our dogs work. So, stand by for plenty of that. But first, let me relate my last season. I tracked Flick's mileage. He averaged twenty-five miles a day, over almost fifty days in the field. I'm a lousy shooter, and okay trainer … so I'll attribute his stamina to my dumb luck, and his performance dog food.
If you want to watch your dog in the field day after day, heed some of the advice I got from Doctor Tim Hunt, a veterinarian, sled dog racer, and developer of the food Flick eats. He says the fuel you put in your dog directly impacts his ability to hunt hard, especially on a long hunting trip. He should know. His food has powered a bunch of Iditarod winners … and my guy Flick.
In this video, you'll learn what the key ingredients are in a dog food, how they work, and why. Hint: the most important component in your dog food is probably NOT what you think it is.

programme.title: Bird dog training: one (baby) step at a time
programme.desc: Dogs learn in a linear fashion, so in this video Scott shows you how important it is to break a complex task into smaller pieces. Training one piece at a time ensures a compliant, happy, peak-performing hunting buddy.

My name is Dallas Cota and I was hooked after a close friend took me out for 5 miserable days on an Alberta Bighorn sheep hunt. A couple years later, I harvested my Bighorn and soon after that, I booked a Dall's sheep hunt in the Yukon. programme.title: Largest Public Land Ram in Utah 194"

He has worked for the Emery County Sheriff's Office for 30 years where he is currently employed as a captain. He has been a member of the Utah FNAWS for the last 10 years and through this he is able to share his passion for the outdoors & wild sheep. In December of 2015 he drew the highly coveted Rocky Mountain Bighorn Sportsman's permit. This tag gave him the opportunity to hunt sheep from the beginning of September to December 31st on almost any open units in the state. He hunted every opportunity that he had he could in pursuit of his dream ram. On November 30th things came together for him and he was able to harvest a very magnificent ram. With an unofficial green score of 194" this ram will be the largest public land ram ever killed in the state of Utah.

programme.desc:
Welcome to Our Wyld Life where host Kristy Titus and her husband, Yogi, take viewers along on their day-to-day lives, full of adventure. After relocating to Wyoming, hunting, outdoor and shooting sports recreation are literally in their backyard. The couple is truly making their home on the range while developing their new homestead and enjoying life in the cowboy state.
In our premiere episode, we show you a little bit of what it's like being a Wyoming resident, in the winter. After a tough start, Kristy makes it a great week with familiar faces and many new ones, in what is one of the most fun shows of the year! If you didn't make it in 2023, it's a must to attend next year! Also, you'll be introduced to the newest (and longest eared) members of the family! Kristy shows off her baby mules...lots more of the mules to come! When they aren't out on an adventure trekking deep into the backcountry with their horses and mules, you'll find them preparing for the next opportunity to do so.
Our Wyld Life presents the journey of life out west in Wyoming.

programme.title: Largest Public Land Ram in Utah 194"
programme.desc: We were very fortunate to play a roll in capturing Kyle Ekker's hunt on film. Kyle Ekker grew up in Green River Utah where he developed his love of hunting, chasing mulies on the Book Cliffs. He has worked for the Emery County Sheriff's Office for 30 years where he is currently employed as a captain. He has been a member of the Utah FNAWS for the last 10 years and through this he is able to share his passion for the outdoors & wild sheep. In December of 2015 he drew the highly coveted Rocky Mountain Bighorn Sportsman's permit. This tag gave him the opportunity to hunt sheep from the beginning of September to December 31st on almost any open units in the state. He hunted every opportunity that he had he could in pursuit of his dream ram. On November 30th things came together for him and he was able to harvest a very magnificent ram. With an unofficial green score of 194" this ram will be the largest public land ram ever killed in the state of Utah.

programme.title: Hunting with a Lost Lemming: Okayest Hunter's 2022 deer hunting season kickoff!
programme.desc:
The crew from the Okayest Hunter podcast thought it'd be a good idea to start a hunting show, but they wanted to do something different, and it needed to align with the brand, mission, and ethos of the Okayest Hunter. Basically, it can't be too serious. So we thought, hey, let's make the "Office" show, but for hunting.
Our hunting season is chock full of humility as we miss place things, take too long to pick out our tree, injure ourselves, miss deer, lose arrows, and more. However, we had one of our best and most fun seasons yet! Follow along as we release new episodes as our 2022 deer hunting season unfolds. We assure you it'll be worth getting all the way to the end!
Cheers to chasing shooter bucks in the deer woods and never passing on what makes you happy! We hope you can relate as we share our shenanigans with everyone!
Okayest Hunter Show, season one: We'll See How it Goes, Episode one: Hunting with a lost lemming.

Dropped - S02:E04 - Now or Never
programme.desc: As the mist drifts past the craggy top of Fish Hook, the crew's shapes slowly come into view right where the ram had been resting. Did they fire without Chris hearing the sound?

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S01:E02 - Naturally Dramatic
programme.desc: This episode describes the greatest miracle of nature that could be created by the human brain. The Loch Ness monster. It looks that is does not exist but thousands of visitors still come to see the lovely lake and to hear tales about it. Not only Nessi, but the Scottish high lands are the miracle of nature.Then we quickly visit Andalusia and remove our hat in front of the majestic mountains of Sierra Nevada.The deepest lake in the world is found in Siberia. We will talk about Baikal, the natural miracle of Russia.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S01:E03 - Naturally Diverse
programme.desc: The episode focuses on the Arabian peninsula. The endless red desert in Oman contrasts with Yemen ́s island of Socotra. The endemic crabs from Socotra compete with sea turtles who gather on a single beach in Oman to lay their eggs. And, it is also claimed that the petrified rock formation is of Noah's Ark.

programme.title: The Luxury Travel Show - S01:E05 - Parrot Cay and Algave
programme.desc: Portugal’s Algarve region has long attracted holidaymakers looking to relax and soak up the sun. Portugal is also quickly becoming known for its great tasting wines. But if Europe is too crowded for your travel tastes then how about the private island resort of Parrot Cay in the Caribbean Turks and Caicos Islands, where you can escape, relax and recharge your batteries in the lap of luxury.

programme.title: Royal Documentaries - S01:E30 - Prince William And Prince Harry Prisoners Of Celebrity
programme.desc: Two young men who have had to cope with extraordinarily challenging events and circumstances as, together, they have gone on to change the face of the British royal family and carve meaningful roles for themselves in the modern world. Made in 1999 two years after the death of their mother, Princess Diana, this original and touching documentary examines the lives of the royal princes, the legacy of their mother, the responsibilities of being a royal - and what the future holds for them.

programme.title: Dropped - S04:E01 - To Be Alive
programme.desc: Chris and Casey Keefer check out video entries to pick a lucky pair to come with them to Alaska. The hunters meet each other at the airport for the first time. Casey and Kaid get Dropped off, while Chris and the rest face delays at the hangar.

programme.title: Dropped - S04:E02 - Separation Anxiety
programme.desc: The weather in Alaska eases up just enough for Chris and Kaid to make it to their destination and catch some food. Meanwhile, Casey and R.L. have already set up camp, gearing up for moose season. The brothers need to get used to the idea of being dropped off separately for the first time.

programme.title: Dropped - S04:E03 - Predators Prowl
programme.desc: Chris and Kaid were getting their rafts set up, while Casey and R.L. started looking around for black bears and moose. Just then, Chris and Kaid noticed a predator making its way towards their campsite.

programme.title: Dropped - S04:E04 - Cloudy Days
programme.desc: It's the second day of hunting season, and Chris and Kaid are still on the lookout for big game. They head downstream to see if they can find a better spot to catch some fish. Meanwhile, Casey and R.L. feast on salmon, getting some much-needed protein. Huge storm clouds are pouring over Alaska.

programme.title: Dropped - S04:E05 - Soaked Spirits
programme.desc: R.L. shares with Casey about the tough times that helped him understand why 'Be Alive' matters so much. Chris and Kaid are stuck in the tent because of the harsh Alaskan weather. Meanwhile, Casey and R.L. manage to find some food.

programme.title: Desperate Hours - S01:E01 - Volcanoes
programme.desc: The Greatest Show on Earth is also the most ferocious. Desperate Hours looks at the destructive force of volcanoes and examines the eruptions in Montserrat which devastated half a Caribbean Island, the 1973 eruption on the Icelandic island of Heimaey, the 2010 eruption Eyjafjallajökull which blocked air travel in Europe, the Merapi eruption in Indonesia, and Mount Nyiragongo in Congo, and the super-volcano in Yellowstone.

programme.title: Desperate Hours - S01:E02 - Earthquake
programme.desc: When the Earth really moves, it means disaster on an epic scale. Desperate Hours looks at the destructive force of earthquakes and looks at the 2015 Kathmandu earthquake in Nepal, the 2008 Sichuan earthquake in China where an estimated 10,000 children were trapped in collapsed school buildings, a 1960 Puerto Mont earthquake in Chile, the 2010 Port-au-Princ earthquake in Haiti, and the 2005 Kashmir earthquake in Pakistan.

programme.title: Desperate Hours - S01:E03 - Epidemic
programme.desc: Desperate Hours looks at major epidemics including the African Ebola outbreak in Sudan which eventually led to cases in the United State and England, the Indian Smallpox outbreak in Bihar, the African Cholera outbreak, the SARS outbreak in Guanghzhou China, and the Bird Flu of Hong Kong.

programme.title: Desperate Hours - S01:E04 - Wind
programme.desc: Desperate Hours looks at the destructive power of wind. From the devastating power of Hurricane Katrina in New Orleans to the destructive Cyclone Nargis in Myanmar, the 1960 storm Hurricane Donna in Florida, Tornado Joplin in Missouri, and Hurricane Sandy in New York.

programme.title: Desperate Hours - S01:E05 - Fire
programme.desc: The blazing terror of a fire can match anything in creation for sheer menace. Desperate Hours looks at the destructive force of fires including the Black Saturday Bushfires in Victoria Australia, the Station Nightclub fire in Rhode Island, the L'Innovation Department Store fire in Brussels Belgium, the Armoury fire in Lagos Nigeria, and the Binhai New Development Zone Fire in Tianjin China.

programme.title: Fight to Survive - S03:E07 - Iraqi Sniper Attack
programme.desc: On deployment in Anbar Province, Marine Corp Master Sergeant Buck Doyle throws himself in harms way to save a fallen comrade from an Iraqi sniper and becomes a target himself.

programme.title: Fight to Survive - S03:E08 - Lightning Strike
programme.desc: A bass fishing trip goes horribly wrong when a bolt of lightning strikes their boat, leaving Seventeen-year-old Christian Neal burned and unconscious and his father Gabe blown into the water and paralyzed. It will take a miracle to save them.

programme.title: Fight to Survive - S03:E09 - Mountain Lion Attack
programme.desc: Marine Anne Hjelle was mountain biking when she was ripped off her bike by a mountain lion. Anne fought back even as the big cat shredded her face in its jaws. Surviving the attack was only the beginning of Anne's incredible fight to survive.

programme.title: Fight to Survive - S03:E10 - Soul of a Survivor
programme.desc: Craig DeMartino examines the stories of other survivors he's met across the season. Their survival stories are all different, but Craig discovers that these survivors share more in common than you might think.

Desperate Hours looks at the destructive force of fires including the Black Saturday Bushfires in Victoria Australia, the Station Nightclub fire in Rhode Island, the L'Innovation Department Store fire in Brussels Belgium, the Armoury fire in Lagos Nigeria, and the Binhai New Development Zone Fire in Tianjin China.

programme.title: Fight to Survive - S03:E07 - Iraqi Sniper Attack
programme.desc: On deployment in Anbar Province, Marine Corp Master Sergeant Buck Doyle throws himself in harms way to save a fallen comrade from an Iraqi sniper and becomes a target himself.

programme.title: Fight to Survive - S03:E08 - Lightning Strike
programme.desc: A bass fishing trip goes horribly wrong when a bolt of lightning strikes their boat, leaving Seventeen-year-old Christian Neal burned and unconscious and his father Gabe blown into the water and paralyzed. It will take a miracle to save them.

programme.title: Royal Documentaries - S01:E27 - Diana And Sarah The Royal Wives Of Windsor Part 1
programme.desc: As royal wives, both Diana and Fergie experienced a life filled with loneliness and sadness, despite their high hopes of bringing change to the House of Windsor. What was supposed to be their 'fairy-tale' lives ended up being far from that reality.

programme.title: Wardens - S02:E03 - Operation Waterfall
programme.desc: Snow in Montana makes the water dangerous, but the yearly boat float goes on. Watch Montana Game Wardens as they check the rivers to keep boaters safe and following the rules.

programme.title: Dropped - S02:E05 - Saddle Sores
programme.desc: The guys are feeling great as they leave sheep territory, but the 22-hour trip to Tom-Tom, the first moose camp, feels endless. It'll take them two long days of riding to get there. As they head into moose land with a successful sheep packed up high, trouble always seems just around the corner on their journey. After riding for eight hours, issues start cropping up.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S01:E04 - Naturally Exotic
programme.desc: This Episode of Miracles of Nature takes you on a journey from the Antigua in the Caribbean to the favourite of climbers - the Blue Mountains of New South Wales, Australia and then back to the Caribbean to admore in the beauty of The British Virgin Islands with stunning white beaches and turquoise waters.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S01:E05 - Naturally Fierce
programme.desc: Visit the wintry North Pole from the comfort of your settee as this episode takes us on a journey to the icy Artic and then to Quebec to watch the most southernly fjord set at low tide, before journeying on to Alberta to take in the magnitude of the Sasquachuan River as it makes its way through the Rocky Mountains.

programme.title: The Luxury Travel Show - S01:E07 - Uga Bay, Sri Lanka and Istanbul
programme.desc: The Luxury Travel Show heads to the idyllic resort of Uga Beach in Sri Lanka for some unusual fine dining locations, with tall tables in the swimming pool and dug-out sunken tables in the sand. Then it’s off to Istanbul with a stay in one of the city’s best hotels - which has been transformed from a derelict tobacco factory into a palace fit for royalty.

programme.title: Royal Documentaries - S01:E28 - Diana And Sarah The Royal Wives Of Windsor Part 2
programme.desc: Diana, Princess of Wales, and Sarah, Duchess of York both married into the Queen's family, leaving in the midst of scandals, though their exits were quite different. Sadly, Diana passed away, while Sarah survived to start anew. Over time, their struggles can be better understood, and this documentary explores those challenges...

programme.title: Wardens - S02:E04 - Operation Snow Cat
programme.desc: Montana Game Wardens ride snowmobiles through the mountains in winter. It's elk hunting season, so they also make sure everyone is following the hunting rules.

programme.title: Dropped - S02:E06 - Church on the Mountain
programme.desc: In the Yukon, decisions can change everything in a heartbeat, especially in such a tough landscape. The brothers are closing in on the enormous mountain grizzly, now just 500 yards away, and it's up to Chris to make the call.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S01:E06 - Naturally Forged
programme.desc: In this episode of Miracles of Nature visits several different islands. Expect to see the breathtaking terrace rocks of Taiwan and the majestic volcano on the mythic island of Bali. On to the island of Jersey, after which a part of New York is named, and finally we visit the spectacular Madeira, which features an amazing variety of landscapes despite being a few kilometres in length.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature - S01:E07 - Naturally Majestic
programme.desc: Follow in the footsteps of Indiana Jones. In this episode of Miracles of Nature we visit the wonders of the Gobi Desert which is one of the oldest deserts in the world, and then the contrasting lush, green hillsides of northern Mongolian. From there we travel 5000 kilometres to the south east to Jordan and the Dead Sea.

programme.title: The Luxury Travel Show - S01:E09 - Rennes and Provo
programme.desc: This gastronomic tour of Brittany stops off for crêpes in Rennes and Oysters in Cancale before visiting the historic walled city of St Malo. Then on to the island of Providenciales, known locally as Provo, in the Turks and Caicos Caribbean islands with buggy racing on the beach and a spot of shopping for some very expensive wines.

programme.title: The Luxury Travel Show - S01:E10 - Stockholm and Lisbon
programme.desc: For a weekend winter break, Stockholm has got to be one of most beautiful cities to visit. Made up of 14 separate islands, it’s one of the best-preserved and largest mediaeval cities in Europe. Then some summer sun in the Portuguese capitol, Lisbon, for a whistle stop cultural tour of the city and a surfing lesson along the coast.

programme.title: Jim Shockey's Uncharted - S01:E10 - The Ancient Ones
programme.desc: Arctic. Jim and Corey's Arctic adventure starts with Muskox, an animal practically forgotten since pre-historic times in the Arctic.

programme.title: Royal Documentaries - S01:E32 - Prince William Royal Teenage Behind The Scenes
programme.desc: Who's the real person beneath all those glamorous royal photos? This intriguing documentary takes a look into the life of the young man behind the public image.

programme.title: 10 Inch Hero
programme.desc: An artist gets a job at a beachside sandwich shop, where she hangs out with a techie, a flirt, a rocker, a hippie, and a Wiccan.

programme.title: Alien Trespass
programme.desc: After crash landing on the outskirts of a desert town, an alien enlists the help of a local waitress to recapture a monster that has escaped the wreckage of his spaceship in this affectionate, knowing, hilarious send-up of a genreís sillier past.

programme.title: Eavesdrop
programme.desc: Ensemble drama about conversations overheard in a bistro: two chess players see unfolding dramas, a couple on an uncomfortable blind date, a crumbling marriage, and film-noir fans that think they're witnessing a real-life murder.

programme.title: Citizen Duane
programme.desc: CITIZEN DUANE is a comedy/drama about Duane Balfour a teen-aged Don Quixote born into a family of spectacular failure. What starts as a simple schoolyard rivalry snowballs out of control when Duane decides to run for mayor of the tiny town of Ridgeway. If Duane is to succeed, he must not only overcome the powerful incumbents, but also his own inadequacies, public perception, and history itself.

programme.title: Comedy Meets Classic
programme.desc: Created by British comedy duo Carrington-Brown, based in Berlin, and Irish conductor ClA�odhna NA� AodA�in, based in Switzerland. They join forces with "The Swonderful Orchestra" for this exciting, classy, and hilarious music & comedy show.

programme.title: Flirting With Flamenco
programme.desc: When Sylvia's well-meaning dad (Watt) surprises her with a devastating revelation, Sylvia's world is turned upside down. But will she crumble or prove herself at the local flamenco contest? An uplifting feel-good Brit comedy drama, Flirting with Flamenco will have you laughing, crying and feeling empowered to turn your life around.

programme.title: Citizen Duane

programme.title: The Flying Deuces
programme.desc: When two bumbling friends join the French Foreign Legion on a whim, they find themselves in a whirlwind of misadventures, love, and laughter as they attempt to navigate the challenges of military life in a foreign land.

programme.title: Perfect Girl
programme.desc: A coming of age romance for anyone who's ever had a crush. Since high school, Stan and Jenny have had crushes on each other. They wrote letters to one another over school holidays but in person they barely spoke; sharing only the occasional lingering glance and smile. Over the years they fantasized about how perfect they would be as lovers. Ten years later they bump into each other and have the chance to make it a reality, but it's not that simple; self doubt, fear of rejection, of losing their fantasies will hold them back from what could be the perfect union.

programme.title: I Would Have Kissed You
programme.desc: Three months after college graduation, best friends Mattie and Olivia are struggling to write a feature and struggling even more with their love lives. Mattie finds herself in a grey area with her college ex-boyfriend while Olivia clings to the hope that her crush will finally want to be with her (despite his hot new girlfriend.) British Web Awards - Awarded "Best Writing in a Dramedy" and "Best Music" Top Indie Awards -Awarded "Best Humor" WRPN Women's International Film Festival - Awarded "Exceptional Merit Award"

programme.title: The General
programme.desc: When Union spies steal Johnnie Gray's (Buster Keaton) beloved locomotive, the General, he pursues them with the aid of his fiance, Annabelle Lee (Marion Mack) straight through enemy lines. One of the most revered comedies of the silent era.

programme.title: Finding Joy
programme.desc: A struggling writer rediscovers himself, his offbeat family, and what it means to be happy when he meets Joy – a spirited, possibly-dying young woman who asks him to write her obituary.

programme.desc: A coming of age romance for anyone who's ever had a crush. Since high school, Stan and Jenny have had crushes on each other. programme.title: ChatRoom - Depression
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: Your friend seems depressed – how do you handle it? And he’s desperately trying to fit in, but does he have to lose himself in the process?

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - St. Kitts
programme.desc: Sunrise Yoga and a Golf lesson highlight Adventure Day One on the island of St. Kitts. We then paddled our way through the surf with sea kayaking and explored the “Valley of the Giants” as we hiked in St. Kitts’ rainforest. Day three began with learning the hot wax art form technique of Batik and concluded with a sunset catamaran cruise. Wrapping up our visit to “Sugar City” we checked out Brimstone Hill Fortress which sits atop one of the island’s highest peaks and then took in the stilt-dancing excitement of the Moko Jumbies.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Puerto Rico
programme.desc: We feel right at home in the United States Commonwealth of Puerto Rico this week. Day one takes us to El Yunque – the Caribbean National Rainforest – where we experience a natural water slide and swing around for even more fun. We then explore Old San Juan on day two before hopping on the jetskis for a high-speed water tour. On day three, we check out the dramatic Camuy Caves and drink in it’s natural beauty and atmosphere. We finish up on day four with an authentic Puerto Rican cooking lesson and a visit to the historic Arecibo Lighthouse.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Alaska
programme.desc: On toady’s show we’ll travel to the incredible state of Alaska. Watch as we climb the ice walls of the Mendenhall Glacier. We’ll also come face to face with a huge brown bear on Admiralty Island, and experience a fly-fishing adventure that we’ll never forget. Add in a little kayaking and some mountain biking and you have one Awesome Adventure!

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Suicide Race
programme.desc: If you think you love pets, then meet Jackie Jacobson, who’s got an awful lot of animals at her house! And visit an equestrian school in New Jersey to learn more about the beauty and excitement of this equine sport. It’s called “The Suicide Race” by its organizers: is it an innocent horse race steeped in tradition or is it outright abuse of these animals? Lastly, meet Ngoma and Tambo, one of the six sets of twin gorillas in captivity, at their home in the Bronx Zoo.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Belize Butterflies
programme.desc: This episode of “Wild About Animals” is devoted entirely to the beautiful country of Belize. You’ll learn all about the birds and the bees, along with some butterflies as we witness the magical birth of a magnificent creature. Next, we’ll visit a lodge in Belize where the guests can get up close and personal to an extremely mischievous monkey! And we’ll venture out into the Belizean jungle, a place where the evening entertainment is unconventional, to say the least.

programme.title: Ocean Animals
programme.desc: Join Emmy Award-winning Actress, Mariette Hartley, as she travels the globe to bring viewers fascinating stories!

programme.title: Whaddyado - Swine Flu
programme.desc: A 15-year-old teenager suffers from the Swine Flu and nearly dies. We’ll feature the symptoms in case you suffer from the Swine Flu. *A six-year-old boy is faced with a life threatening emergency and needs to call 9-1-1. *A man in Arizona is walking his dogs when a venomous rattlesnake bites him. We will tell you the steps to take in case a rattlesnake bites you. Our Moral Dilemma segment features the social problems caused by “mean girls.”

programme.title: Whaddyado - Shark Attack
programme.desc: A shark attacks and a surfer must ride the waves to escape to the safety of the beach. *A video surveillance system catches a near drowning on camera and the technology is the key to a young girl’s rescue. * A moral dilemma segment deals with peer pressure and the decision to get a tattoo.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Intruder
programme.desc: In this episode, a 12-year old is home alone, when an intruder breaks into his house. Two buddies are snowmobiling when an avalanche buries one of them. It will take a miracle to save him. A Florida family finds an unwelcome guest on their doorstep: A large alligator. And our Moral Dilemma looks at the growing problem of obesity.

programme.title: ChatRoom - Dropping Out of School
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: A friend is thinking about dropping out of school. What are his options? And she tries to laugh it off but mom has a serious drinking problem.

programme.title: ChatRoom - Bias
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: Mom’s prejudices are coming through loud and clear. And how high a price are you willing to pay to join the group?

programme.title: ChatRoom - Cheating
programme.desc: ChatRoom focuses on the ever-changing issues for today’s teens in a format that invites viewers to listen in on the conversation. This week’s topics include: She’s a little tipsy and he needs a ride, how do you handle it? And you forgot to study and there’s a pop quiz, what’s wrong with borrowing a few answers from a buddy?

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Minnesota
programme.desc: This week’s “Awesome Adventure” took us to the land of 10,000 lakes. We first learned how to hook up a team of dogs and let them take us for a ride on a dogsled. We then motored across frozen landscape in snowmobiles before traveling to Buck Hill for snowboarding, skiing and snow tubing. Next, we decided to spend some time indoors, so we headed to the Science Museum of Minnesota and slid over to the Grand Rios indoor water park. Since Minneapolis is home to the world famous Mall of America, we had to check out the mall that has it all. At the mall we visited the world’s largest underground aquarium, rode the Timberland Twister and made our own, Awesome Adventures-style fashion statement.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Canada
programme.desc: On this week’s episode of “Awesome Adventures,” we’ll travel to Canada to visit Vancouver Island, an adventure seekers paradise. We’ll work hand in hand to tackle a high ropes course, and climb the face of a 60 foot cliff. We’ll come face to face with black bears, and enormous whales. And we’ll experience the thrill of snorkeling down the Campbell River.

programme.title: Awesome Adventures - Curacao
programme.desc: This week it's off to the remote Caribbean island of Curacao.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Philadelphia Insectarium
programme.desc: Insects may seem creepy, but a lady at the Philadelphia Insectarium proves that bugs are fun. Next, you’ll meet Moose, one of the largest dogs in the world. Then we’ll travel out into the woods to learn more about bears. Finally, we’ll see a reptile show set in a school.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Best of 1995
programme.desc: This show features some of our favorite stories and moments from last season. We take you to incredible places like the Great Barrier Reef where you’ll learn and experience the underwater world of Australia. We also feature incredible animal rescue stories; the beautiful animals of Africa; as well as tips on learning how to care for our backyard creatures.

programme.title: Wild About Animals - Vancouver Aquariam
programme.desc: This week on Wild About Animals we travel to Vancouver and visit the Marine Mammal Rescue Center. Researcher Bruce McCellan shows us how he uses hairs traps to research Grizzly bears. Then we meet up with Rob Hope of O.W.L. who introduces us to a rescued Great Horned Owl that is about to be released into the wild. And finally, we learn about 3 timber wolves, who were raised to be actors, but didn’t make it in the acting world and are now running free in Grouse Mountain.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Saving Pet
programme.desc: A 16-year-old teenager is struck by lightning and still survives. We’ll tell you what you should do if you find someone struck by lightning. *A dog trainer saves a dog’s life by giving it CPR. We’ll show you how to give CPR to help save your pet. * When a family’s car is stuck in the snow, they nearly die of carbon monoxide poisoning. We‘ll explain how carbon monoxide is the invisible killer and can be avoided. Our Moral Dilemma segment features the growing trend of sexual harassment at work.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Father Heart Attack
programme.desc: A three year old nearly drowns in his family’s swimming pool…he is rescued just in time by his five year old brother. *Father and son are walking home from a basketball game when the father suffers a heart attack…the son bravely gives him CPR and saves his life.*A critter has been disturbing a man’s bird feeder, so he sets up a motion detecting camera in his back yard…the very next night, he discovers it’s a huge black bear.* In our Moral Dilemma this week we take a hard look at teenage drivers and the dangerous distraction of their cell phones.

programme.title: Whaddyado - Kayaking
programme.desc: Camping…a group of teens that are a part of the “Venture Crew” with the boy scouts show us the right and wrong things to do when camping out. *A troublesome bear goes into a family’s home for their dinner leftovers. * Kayaking is a lot of fun but can turn dangerous when trying “White Water” paddling…what do you do if you find yourself in trouble. * A forest fire is approaching your home…have a plan here’s what to do.

programme.title: ChatRoom - Two Moms
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: You’ve made a new friend who’s trying to convince you to do some bad things. And instead of a mom and a dad this kid’s got two moms. Should it matter?

programme.title: ChatRoom - Peer Preasure
programme.desc: An adult host and a panel of four young adults discuss dilemmas, scenarios and situations that are relevant to kids' lives. This week’s topics include: Peer pressure in the form of smoking. And spread the word, these words can hurt. Do you really need to say them?

programme.title: Countdown To Apollo - The Mercury 7
programme.desc: Before Apollo, there was Gemini, and before Gemini, there was the Mercury program. This episode examines Mercury, the first U.S. program to put a man in space. It looks at the people, such as astronaut John Glenn, the events, such as Alan Shephard’s first flight to low earth orbit, and the triumphs of this precursor to Apollo.

programme.title: Countdown To Apollo - Firsts
programme.desc: This episode features the important “firsts” of the Apollo program. From the first satellite launched by the Soviets called Sputnick; to the first man who flew in space named Yuri Gagarin; the first spacewalk to the first live broadcast in space, many of the monumental achievements of the space race are documented.

programme.title: The Apollo Chronicles - Part 4 - Hailed As Heroes
programme.desc: Revel in the emotional achievement and lasting legacy of man’s first steps on the Moon.

programme.title: Life 2.0 - Drones Away
programme.desc: In this episode we explore some of the newest and most innovative uses for drones and reveal how they are becoming increasingly ubiquitous. Much like how the automobile once changed the world, drones are poised to do the same. Could we end up in a society where it’s normal to look up and see the sky abuzz with activity?

programme.desc: This episode looks at how virtual reality will transform our lives.

programme.title: Nature Knows Best - Safer Thanks To Nature

programme.title: Nature Knows Best - Whirlybird

programme.title: Xploration Earth 2050 - Trees Change The Future

programme.title: Xploration Earth 2050 - High Tech Goes Exploring
programme.desc: We have always been interested in the workings of Earth, and high tech is giving them new insights.

programme.title: Xploration Awesome Planet - Students Lead

programme.title: Xploration Awesome Planet - Marvels Of Nature
programme.desc: Philippe Cousteau explores unbelievable marvels of nature across our awesome planet.

programme.title: Xploration Outer Space - Shifting Sands
programme.desc: The last man to walk on the moon was Gene Cernan on the Apollo 17 mission, in 1972. He said, “As we leave the moon, we leave as we came and God willing as we shall return. ”But with Nasa relying on government funding, the path back to the moon has been full of obstacles. This episode examines how each new President has their own vision of space exploration, and why this results in stops and starts in the space program.

programme.title: Xploration Outer Space - Moon to Mars
programme.desc: The moon is the next logical starting point for deep space exploration, and the Artemis missions are headed there. But there are those who think it is a mistake to focus on our closet celestial neighbor. They say we should get to Mars, and once there, turn it into a living planet. The debate rages…on Xploration Outer Space.

programme.title: Xploration Earth 2050 - Virtual Tech Tests Future Tech
programme.desc: This lab creates a blistering desert one minute and a tropical rain forest the next.

programme.title: Xploration Earth 2050 - High Tech Revolutionizes Medicine

programme.title: Life 2.0 - Rise of the Cyborgs

programme.title: Life 2.0 - Big Data
programme.desc: In this episode we pull back the curtain on data science to explore where all this data is coming from and how it’s playing a crucial role in everything from advertising to health care to world policy.

programme.title: DIY Sci - Museum Of Science Boston #2
programme.desc: Host Steve Spangler and his sidekick Higginsworth return to the Museum of Science, Boston, where they take simple demonstrations they’ve done on DIY Sci and make them gigantic! Higgins becomes a human-sized balancing toy and Steve get locked in a cage that’s struck by lightning at the world’s largest Van de Graaf generator.

programme.title: DIY Sci - Bet You Can't
programme.desc: Steve Spangler reveals amazing science tricks that will have you saying to your friends, “I bet you can’t do that!” He’ll show you tricks like how to balance a quarter on the edge of a dollar bill and how to stick your entire head through a hole in a small index card.

programme.title: Stuart Cooper Films - The Craig Jones Story
programme.desc:
A short documentary telling the story of Craig Jones' sudden rise to success after his upset victory over Leandro Lo at ADCC 2017. After his breakout performance at ADCC, Craig went on to beat many more big names such as Jake Shields In Polaris, and made it to the finals of EBI, where he had a close finals match against Gordon Ryan. Since then Craig has competed in some of the biggest tournaments in the world and his life has changed dramatically. In this film we see that it wasn't always an easy road for him.
Director Stuart Cooper

programme.title: Superfight - Andre Galvao vs Braulio Estima by Stuart Cooper
programme.desc: In this video Andre Galvao looks back on his match with Braulio Estima for the ADCC 2013 Super Fight Title. Then, Andre recaps on some of his most entertaining matches from ADCC 2011, which include; Don Ortega, Gunnar Nelson, Pablo Popovitch, Rousimar "Toquinho" Palhares and Sergio Moraes.

programme.title: Tap Out Challenge - Oceanside
programme.desc: On October 15th at the picturesque Oceanside, CA, Charles Rials embarked on an incredible BJJ journey, challenging strangers from all walks of life to tap me out and claim $100. But there was a twist that none of them saw coming! Win or Lose, they got the MONEY!!! What they all shared was the courage to step up, the passion to engage, and the heart of a warrior. This video isn't just about BJJ or the challenge — it's a celebration of the human spirit, perseverance, and the unexpected twists that life (and jiu jitsu) can throw our way. Join Charles in this heartwarming, adrenaline-pumping journey where every challenge was met with respect, and every challenger was met with a surprise. Whether you're a BJJ enthusiast or someone who loves to witness genuine human moments, this video has something special for you.

programme.title: ADCC - Denver Opens
programme.desc: The Opens make their way to the mile high city where the best martial arts from the US look to stake their claim for supremacy as the circuit heats up. In this heart-pounding instalment, we bring you all the action from the epic showdown held in the magnificent city of Denver. Former UFC Strawweight Champion of the World Rose Namajunas known for her exceptional martial arts abilities, Rose is now ready to put her skills to the ultimate test in the realm of grappling. Witness her transition from the cage to the mats, as she grapples her way through some of the most intense matches of her career. ADCC Opens superstar and prodigy 16-year-old phenom, Helena Craver, steps onto the mats to showcase her unparalleled talent. With her sights set on glory, she aims to conquer the teenage, adults, and absolute divisions a feat that has never been done before. In a clash of titans, long time elite grappler Ryan Aitkens, a formidable competitor in his own right, is set to go head-to-head against the multiple-time world champion, Mateus Lutes. Brace yourself for an explosive battle between these two grappling juggernauts, as they leave everything on the mats in pursuit of victory.

programme.title: Chef Swap at the Beach - Chef Swap At The Beach: Steak And Eggs Swap
programme.desc: Steak and Eggs are a breakfast staple, but this hearty combination certainly doesn't have to be boring. Chef Mason pushes the limit of this classic dish as he challenges Chef Derick Carrozza of Filet’s and Chef Casey Blake of Drunken Jack’s to both bring their “A-game” in each other’s kitchens — or should we say their "egg-game"?

programme.title: Q: Alabama’s Barbecue Legends - Q: Alabama’s Barbecue Legends
programme.desc: The story of Alabama barbecue can’t be told in sentences. It’s told through whiffs of smoke, buckets of sauce and friendly nods across the counter. See how a simple dish has become a culinary anthem for Alabama.

programme.title: Love On the Rocks - Tying the Knot at 13,000 Feet
programme.desc: A romantic trip to Colorado takes a windy turn when Jason pushes Tayler, despite her hesitation, to summit Mt. Democrat in 70 mph winds and -19 degree weather.

programme.title: Love On the Rocks - A Newly-Wed Recipe for Disaster
programme.desc: Jason loves mountain biking. Tayler prefers to read a book. Jason is up for any adventure tossed at him. Tayler likes to be a bit more prepared. Will the adventures that await in Arkansas leave the couple questioning if they have anything in common?

programme.title: Love On the Rocks - Theodora's Room
programme.desc: Tayler and Jason travel to Eureka Springs, Arkansas, a town with a rich history and home to one of the most haunted hotels in America, The Crescent. Jason convinces Tayler to stay one night, but will that stay lead to a night they don't want to remember?

programme.title: Love On the Rocks - Marriage Lows
programme.desc: Jason experiences insecurity about challenges that the couple are, quite literally, dropped into. From falling out of the sky to a rappel into a dark cave, will the couple be able to work together or will they end up stranded in the dark?

programme.title: Four Corners - FOUR CORNERS: ARIZONA
programme.desc: Today, Jamie is up with his surprise itinerary in Arizona - taking in the Grand Canyon, Tucson, Tombstone and many other adventures in between... But how will the trip go down with the others?!

programme.title: Four Corners - FOUR CORNERS: UTAH
programme.desc: For this episode, Ben’s planned an EPIC 48 hours in Utah, starting in Salt Lake City before venturing down to Zion National Park - but what will the other guys make of his itinerary?

programme.title: Four Corners - FOUR CORNERS: NEW MEXICO
programme.desc: This time, Mike’s planned 48 hours in New Mexico... And he's determined to show the guys as much of it as possible!! From the White Sands National Park, to Hatch, Santa Fe, Albuquerque and Taos! How do you think he’ll get on??!

programme.title: Four Corners - FOUR CORNERS: COLORADO
programme.desc: Finishing their Four Corners adventure, it’s Barry’s turn, and he’s not exactly known for his organization skills! Watch as he takes the friends from Grand Junction to the Grand Mesa and on to Vail and Boulder... How will the guys judge him, and who will be the overall winner?!

programme.title: USA Through the Great Outdoors - USA Through the Great Outdoors
programme.desc: Place is inextricably linked to who we are as human beings. See the American Great Outdoors in its purest and most authentic light – through the eyes of locals.

programme.title: USA Through Food - USA Through Food
programme.desc: A journey through the USA, through the diverse food scenes of six vibrant cities.

programme.title: Small Town, Big Story - Home of the Mushroom

Each is determined to delight - and outdo - the other with unforgettable experiences that showcase the state's rich culture. Elsa kicks off the competition with a classic Kentucky breakfast, a recipe she learned from top Chef Ouita Michel at her Holly Hill Cooking Studio. programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 447 - Up Next Fighting 13 part 1
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Up Next Fighting 13 part 1 from the Commerce Hotel and Casino in Southern California. First up, striker Bryen Dao takes on brawler Ferrin Marcelin in the featherweight division and Aiden Ingram steps into the cage with Steve Mora in a bantamweight bout. Also on this card Carlos Figueroa looks to break Artem Afanasenko's undefeated streak. In the main event, Christopher "Taco" Padilla puts his lightweight title on the line when he faces his toughest opponent yet with five time UFC veteran Justin Janyes.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 451 - Up Next Fighting 13 part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Up Next Fighting 13 part 2 from the Commerce Hotel and Casino in Southern California. Starting off in the bantamweight division, Jonathan Powell steps into the cage with veteran grappler Will Holguin. In a featherweight bout, striker Jonny O'Neill takes on wrestler Eudardo Zarate with the winner moving on to a title opportunity. Also watch as Adam Garcia and Zachary Kraschinsky take to the ring in a lightweight bout. With two titles on the line in the featured bout, the rising star UNF Featherweight title and the California State featherweight title in the rising stars division, Stone Lavelle and his opponient Sean Crenshaw battle it out for the two belts.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 430- Dynamite Fighting Show 26 part 1
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Dynamite Fighting Show 26 part 1 from the Traian Aena in Râmnicu Vâlcea, Romania for a great night of fights. Up first in the middle weight division Denis Ceausu faces Andrei Varga. In the open weight division with a huge weight differential Rodrigo Mineiro, kickboxing world champion takes on boxer Bogdan Bestea for a boxing versus kickboxing contest. Watch as Alex Leautaund of the Netherlands takes on Romania's Mihai Desrobitu in a cruiserweight boxing bout.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 433 - Dynamite Fighting Show 26 part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Dynamite Fighting Show 26 part 2 from the Traian Aena in Râmnicu Vâlcea, Romania for a great night of fights. First up, a Superfight in the welterweight division, Bogdan Floristean versus Ionel Balan. In the women's lightweight division Maria Nitescu takes on Andreea Cebuc to determine the Baddest Woman in Romania. Also on this episode in the open division Tibor Varga of Hungary steps into the ring with Romania's Bogdan Nastase in a David versus Goliath duel.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 437 - Dynamite Fighting Show 26 part 3
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Dynamite Fighting Show 26 part 3 from the Traian Aena in Râmnicu Vâlcea, Romania for a great night of boxing and kickboxing fights. In the welterweight division Vinicius Bereta takes on Valentin Mavrodin in a Brazil versus Romania bout. In the open weight division Tolea Ciumac steps into the ring with Valentin Lambagiu with 100 pounds and over 20 years difference between the two fighters for a David versus Goliath duel. In the main event, Portugal's Iuri Fernandes faces Romania's Bogdan Stoica, with a stunning 58 wins to his name, in the Heavyweight division.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 453 - DMG Boxing presents Night of Champions IV part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents DMG Boxing Night of Champions IV part 2 from The Fox Theater in Pomona, California. Starting off with a female bout, undefeated fighters Olympian Brianda Cruz and Susana Lopez step into the ring to fight for their perfect record. In the main event is another battle of the undefeated as David Romero takes on Pedro Valencia who is coming off of a three year hiatus.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 411 - Clan Wars 50
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Clan Wars 50 from Belfast. Up first a lightweight title bout with Dara O'Sullivan versus Sam "Slam" Simon, Nathan Chambers squares off against Brian Damian in the featherweight division, Lewis Byrne faces Latvian Juris Ruckanovs and Mike McBride steps into the ring with Billy Sutherland in the Bantamweight division with a title on the line. In the main event for the Superlightweight title, Peter Halpenny takes on Jamie McCaugherty.
